  "title": "welder",
  "description": "<ul>\n  <li>Reading and interpreting blueprints: Understanding designs, specifications, and diagrams to determine the appropriate welding process.</li>\n  <li>Operating welding equipment: Utilizing various welding techniques like MIG, TIG, and arc welding.</li>\n  <li>Sourcing and preparing materials: Measuring, cutting, and preparing metal pieces for welding.</li>\n  <li>Performing welding tasks: Joining metal parts with precision and accuracy.</li>\n  <li>Inspecting welds: Ensuring structural integrity and quality.</li>\n  <li>Maintaining equipment and tools: Ensuring proper functioning and safety.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Depending on the specific role and industry, welders may also be responsible for:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Shaping and polishing metal after welding: Ensuring a smooth and polished finish.</li>\n  <li>Working with different types of metals: Handling various alloys and materials.</li>\n  <li>Following safety regulations: Adhering to safety procedures and using personal protective equipment.</li>\n  <li><br></li>\n</ul>",
